he path to salvation. Bringing a medical lens to the religious discourse, this text demonstrates that rather than rejecting medical traditions, early Christianity developed through creatively integrating them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBrainxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aMedicinexReligious aspectsxChristianityxHistory of doctrinesyEarly church, ca. 30-600. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishz978311099291508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107664930 cprintz978052038767640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520387683?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520387683423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520387683/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099291-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-UCY